1this is an example in this lesson

#include <iostream>
 
using namespace std;
 
int main()
{
  cout<<"HEY, you, I'm alive! Oh, and Hello World!\n";
  cin.get();
 
  return 1;
}


1.1How your program first be executed?  -----main function
       int main(){}
        |    
      return 
      type
1.2"# include < name of header file> "  -----preprocessor.

1.3 Display text  ---cout<<
                          "\n" ---a character stands for a new line;

1.4 cin.get() ---reads the input and expect the user to hit the return key
1.5 return 0 for success (only for main function).
2. comment ---"//"for one line comment
              "/*~*/ for multiple lines

